&lt;h2 id=&#34;research-topics&#34;&gt;Research topics&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-volatile optical phase-change materials&lt;/strong&gt; - Novel chalcogenide phase-change materials (e.g. Ge2Sb2Te5) with distinct optical and electrical contrasts between two stable states: amorphous and crystalline phases, with unique applications in photonics, electronics and optoelectronics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Low dimensional opto-electronic devices&lt;/strong&gt; -  Low dimensional materials, especially 2D materials, with execeptional optoelectronic properties and CMOS-compatible fabrication process can be used for high pferformance photodetectors, modulators, sensors, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reflective nanodisplays&lt;/strong&gt; -  Reflective color displays based on non-volatile materials show zero static power comsuption, high resolution and electrical modulation capability which have promising applications in next generation display technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Active optical metasurfaces&lt;/strong&gt; -  Optical metasurfaces hold considerable promise for future advances in fundamental optics and novel optical applications. Introducing active functionalities to metasurfaces is an essential step to the development of practicle optical components and devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
